sentences.en: As of 2004 Western Europe and the USA accounted for approximately 37% each of the World Market whilst Japan accounted for just over 15%.

sentences.en: This is a decrease since 1990 when the same group accounted for 31.1 per cent.

sentences.en: It is worth noting that manufacturing companies only accounted for 12% of our random sample.
